      "amount": "8 oz",
      "notes": "Thinly sliced"
    },
    {
      "name": "Fresh Parsley",
      "amount": "1 cup",
      "notes": "Chopped"
    },
    {
      "name": "Powdered Sugar",
      "amount": "2 tbsp",
      "notes": "For dusting"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Rinse the cod fillets and pat them dry with paper towels.",
    "Season the cod with garlic powder, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Heat the olive oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Sear the cod for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until golden brown.",
    "Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and bake for 8-10 minutes, or until cooked through.",
    "While the cod is baking, mix the lemon juice, sliced pickling cucumbers, and thinly sliced red onion in a bowl.",
    "Toss the chopped parsley with the cucumber mixture and season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Transfer the cod to the molcajete and top with the pickled vegetable mixture.",
    "Dust the top of the cod with powdered sugar.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
